org.eclipse.rdf4j.query.parser.sparql

Class NegatedPropertySet

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.rdf4j.query.parser.sparql.NegatedPropertySet
  • Deprecated. 
    since 3.0. This feature is for internal use only: its existence, signature or behavior may change without warning from one release to the next.

    @Deprecated
 @InternalUseOnly
public class NegatedPropertySet
extends Object
    A negated property set is a SPARQL construction of the form {?X !(uri|^uri) ?Y}. This class is a temporary representation used by the parser. It is converted by the TupleExprBuilder into a set of joins and filters on regular statement patterns.
    Author:
    Jeen
